graphAlgorithms

Class CloserToFarthestPoint_ClusterFormation

  • java.lang.Object
    • graphAlgorithms.CloserToFarthestPoint_ClusterFormation

  • public class CloserToFarthestPoint_ClusterFormation
extends java.lang.Object
    CloserToFarthestPoint_ClusterFormation class forms the clusters with schools closer to the farthest schools. It gives the route to be traversed from the kitchen through this each of the clusters formed.
    Author:
    Abhishek Joshi, Anand Tirthgirikar, Sandesh Prabhu

      • clusterFormation

        public java.util.List<School> clusterFormation(School farthestSchool)
        This method gives the cluster of schools closer to the farthestSchool. It checks if new schools can be added to the cluster around current farthest school using the school demands and vehicle capacity remaining.
        Parameters:
        farthestSchool - Contains the current farthest point
        Returns:
        The list containing all the schools in current cluster

      • canCurrentSchoolBeAddedToCurrentFarthestPointCluster

        public boolean canCurrentSchoolBeAddedToCurrentFarthestPointCluster(java.util.List<School> currentFarthestPointCluster,
                                                                    School newSchool)
        This method checks if the newSchool can be added to the cluster around the current farthest school. It checks this based on the service time and travel time. It uses Traveling Salesman Problem algorithm.
        Parameters:
        currentFarthestPointCluster - Contains the list of schools in current cluster
        newSchool - Contains the new school that needs to be added to the list
        Returns:
        true or false
